Setting Wlan mode via telux::wlan::IWlanDeviceManager::setMode API configures Wlan subsystem for
enabled number of AP and Sta. Each enabled AP/Sta will have assigned telux::wlan::Id.

First enabled AP will get telux::wlan::Id::PRIMARY, second enabled AP will get
telux::wlan::Id::SECONDARY, and so on.
Similarly, the first enabled Sta will get telux::wlan::Id::PRIMARY and second enabled Sta will get
telux::wlan::Id::SECONDARY, and so on.

Depending on whether Sta is enabled (number of enabled Sta is not 0) or not, each enabled
AP/Sta will get its settings from configuration files listed below:

If Stan mode is not enabled, AP configuration files are located at:
    AP telux::wlan::Id::PRIMARY      /etc/misc/wifi/hostapd.conf
    AP telux::wlan::Id::SECONDARY    /etc/misc/wifi/hostapd-wlan1.conf
    AP telux::wlan::Id::TERTIARY     /etc/misc/wifi/hostapd-wlan2.conf
If Sta mode is enabled, configuration files are located at:
    STA telux::wlan::Id::PRIMARY     /etc/misc/wifi/wpa_supplicant.conf
    AP telux::wlan::Id::PRIMARY      /etc/misc/wifi/sta_mode_hostapd.conf
    AP telux::wlan::Id::SECONDARY    /etc/misc/wifi/hostapd-wlan2.conf